{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QpZbLUrcpuknqKax6X1B89","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create the report.\n\n## Project Structure Exploration Report\n\nI've conducted a thorough exploration of the Cloche project. Here's what I found:\n\n### **1. Overall Directory Layout**\n\n```\n/workspace/\n├── cmd/                          # Three binaries\n│   ├── cloche/                   # CLI client\n│   ├── cloched/                  # Daemon\n│   └── cloche-agent/             # In-container entrypoint\n├── internal/                     # Core application logic\n│   ├── domain/                   # Domain types & validation\n│   ├── ports/                    # Interfaces (hexagonal arch)\n│   ├── adapters/                 # Implementations\n│   │   ├── agents/               # Agent adapters\n│   │   ├── docker/               # Docker runtime\n│   │   ├── grpc/                 # gRPC server\n│   │   ├── sqlite/               # SQLite store\n│   │   ├── web/                  # Web handler\n│   │   └── local/                # Local runtime\n│   ├── dsl/                      # Workflow DSL parser & lexer\n│   ├── engine/                   # Workflow execution engine\n│   ├── host/                     # Host workflow executor\n│   ├── agent/                    # Agent runner\n│   ├── config/                   # Configuration\n│   ├── evolution/                # Self-evolution system\n│   ├── logstream/                # Log parsing & broadcasting\n│   └── protocol/                 # Result/status protocols\n├── .cloche/                      # Project configuration (gitignored runs)\n│   ├── develop.cloche            # Container workflow\n│   ├── host.cloche               # Host orchestration workflow\n│   ├── Dockerfile                # Container image\n│   ├── prompts/                  # Agent prompt templates\n│   ├── scripts/                  # Host-side scripts\n│   ├── overrides/                # Container file overrides\n│   ├── evolution/                # Self-evolution config\n│   ├── output/                   # Output files from runs\n│   └── [run-id]/                 # Runtime state for each run\n├── api/                          # protobuf definitions\n├── test/                         # Integration tests\n├── examples/                     # Example projects\n├── docs/                         # Documentation & design docs\n├── Makefile, go.mod, go.sum\n└── Database files (cloche.db)\n```\n\n### **2. Current State of cmd/ and internal/ Directories**\n\n**cmd/** contains 3 main binaries:\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` + health, init, poll, orchestrate commands with tests\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go` - daemon\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche-agent/main.go` - container entrypoint\n\n**internal/** has 13 subdirectories with comprehensive Go implementation:\n- 33 test files total (extensive test coverage)\n- Key modules: `domain/`, `dsl/`, `engine/`, `host/`, `adapters/`\n\n### **3. Existing Tests**\n\n**33 test files** covering:\n- Lexer & Parser tests (DSL parsing)\n- Domain types validation\n- All adapter implementations (Docker, SQLite, gRPC, Web)\n- Host executor with output mapping tests\n- Integration tests (smoke_test.go, evolution_test.go)\n- Log parsing and streaming\n- Configuration validation\n\n**Notable:** Output mapping feature already has dedicated tests:\n- `internal/domain/output_path_test.go` - 21 comprehensive tests for path evaluation\n- `internal/host/executor_test.go` - Tests for output mapping resolution (lines 373-560+)\n\n### **4. Workflow DSL Files**\n\n**Main Workflow Files:**\n- `/workspace/develop.cloche` - Container workflow (implement → test → vet → build → fix)\n- `/workspace/.cloche/host.cloche` - Host orchestration (ready-tasks → prepare-prompt → develop → merge → cleanup)\n- `/workspace/.cloche/develop.cloche` - Updated version in .cloche/ directory\n\n**Host Scripts:**\n- `ready-tasks.sh` - Fetches JSON from `bd ready`\n- `prepare-prompt.sh` - Prepares prompt for development\n- `merge-to-main.sh` - Merges results to main\n- `cleanup-run.sh` - Cleans up run artifacts\n\n### **5. Implementation Status: Wire Output Mapping Feature**\n\nThe **wire output mapping feature is already FULLY IMPLEMENTED** as per the design document from 2026-03-09:\n\n**Completed Components:**\n\n1. **Domain Types** (`/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`):\n   - ✓ `OutputPath` struct with `Segments []PathSegment`\n   - ✓ `OutputMapping` struct with `EnvVar` and `Path` fields\n   - ✓ `Wire.OutputMap` field to hold mappings\n   - ✓ `PathSegment` with `Kind` (SegmentField/SegmentIndex), `Field`, and `Index`\n   - ✓ `Evaluate(raw []byte)` method on OutputPath (lines 75-115)\n\n2. **Lexer** (`/workspace/internal/dsl/lexer.go`):\n   - ✓ `TokenInt` added for integer literals (line 81)\n   - ✓ Tests updated with integer handling\n\n3. **Parser** (`/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go`):\n   - ✓ `parseWire()` method (line 376)\n   - ✓ `parseOutputMappings()` method (line 414) \n   - ✓ `parseOutputPath()` method (line 452)\n   - ✓ Full support for `[ KEY = output.path ]` syntax\n\n4. **Validation** (`/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`):\n   - ✓ Duplicate env var mapping detection (lines 214-226)\n   - ✓ Integrated into `Workflow.Validate()` method\n\n5. **Host Executor** (`/workspace/internal/host/executor.go`):\n   - ✓ `resolveOutputMappings()` method (line 22-41)\n   - ✓ Integration into `executeScript()` (lines 87-92)\n   - ✓ Reads source output, evaluates paths, injects env vars\n\n6. **Tests**:\n   - ✓ `output_path_test.go` - 21 test cases for all path evaluation scenarios\n   - ✓ `parser_test.go` - Multiple tests for mapping syntax (lines 429-576)\n   - ✓ `executor_test.go` - Integration tests for output mapping resolution (lines 373-560+)\n\n**Current Usage in host.cloche:**\nThe `/workspace/.cloche/host.cloche` shows mappings in use:\n```\nready-tasks:success -> prepare-prompt [\n  CLOCHE_TASK_ID    = output[0].id,\n  CLOCHE_TASK_TITLE = output[0].title,\n  CLOCHE_TASK_BODY  = output[0].description\n]\n```\n\n### **6. Other Notable Items**\n\n**Design Documents** in `/workspace/docs/plans/`:\n- `2026-03-09-wire-output-mapping-design.md` - Comprehensive design with implementation details\n- `2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md` - Full system architecture\n- Various other design docs for features like host workflows, evolution, subdirectories\n\n**Project Status:**\n- Recent commit (dee4995): \"Disable self-evolution while focusing on orchestrator work\"\n- 389+ test runs in `.cloche/` showing active development\n- Database (cloche.db) with ~35MB active state\n- Multiple successful development runs (develop-firm-peak, develop-glad-jade)\n\n**Evolution System:**\n- Located in `/workspace/internal/evolution/`\n- Currently disabled per recent commit\n- Includes orchestrator, classifier, curator, reflector modules\n\n**Examples:**\n- Ruby calculator, mini-redis, Gemini browser - demonstrating multi-language support\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nThe Cloche project is a sophisticated grow-coding system with:\n- **Fully implemented wire output mapping feature** - The design from March 9 has been completely coded and tested\n- **Comprehensive test coverage** (33 test files)\n- **Hexagonal architecture** with clear separation of domain, ports, and adapters\n- **DSL-based workflow definition** supporting both host and container workflows\n- **Active self-evolution system** (currently paused to focus on orchestration)\n- **Well-documented design** with extensive planning docs\n\nThe feature is production-ready and actively used in the host workflow orchestration."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a51bb6230ba4add61 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 57634\ntool_uses: 35\nduration_ms: 54230</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2613b431-515d-48d3-bbf6-bbabff4e6c49","uuid":"827a6db1-34